            [
                "**Clerical review** encola band review. **Cluster consistency:** si A~B y B~C con alta confianza, A~C debe revisarse si el modelo dice non.",
                "Mecanismo: grafo de auto-edges; detectar contradicción con transitive closure simple.",
                f"Contrato. Entrada: edges auto + juicio non. Salida: needs_review True si contradicción. `{caso}-T3B`.",
                "Aplicación: A-B, B-C auto; A-C non → review. Humano manda.",
            ],
            subtopic_id="S30-T3-B", code_title="cluster_consistency.py",
            code="""
def needs_review(auto_edges, non_pairs):
    # naive: if both endpoints connected via auto to a common chain of length 2
    from collections import defaultdict
    g = defaultdict(set)
    for a, b in auto_edges:
        g[a].add(b); g[b].add(a)
    for a, b in non_pairs:
        # share a neighbor or direct path len 2
        if g[a] & g[b]:
            return True
    return False

print("needs_review", needs_review([("A", "B"), ("B", "C")], [("A", "C")]))
print("human", True)
print("means_fraud", False)
